---
id: dxos.plugin.chess
name: ChessPlugin
version: 0.3.0
extends: [dxos.plugin.chess@0.2.0]
---

Extends chess-2 to introduce operations and services: move validation,
game state transitions, and the chess engine service dependency.

## Extensions

| Term        | URI                            |
|-------------|--------------------------------|
| `type`      | dxos.org/ext/type@1.0          |
| `feat`      | dxos.org/ext/feat@1.0          |
| `test`      | dxos.org/ext/test@1.0          |
| `component` | dxos.org/ext/component@1.0     |
| `op`        | dxos.org/ext/op@1.0            |
| `service`   | dxos.org/ext/service@1.0       |

## Services

```service ChessEngine
  desc: Validates moves and computes game state. May be local (WASM) or remote.
  loading: lazy
  ops:
    validate(board: Board, move: Move) → Move
    legalMoves(board: Board, square: Square) → Square[]
    applyMove(board: Board, move: Move) → Board
  errors:
    EngineNotReady: engine has not finished loading
```

```service GameStore
  desc: Persists and replicates Game state via ECHO.
  ops:
    create(white: Player, black: Player) → Game
    load(id: string) → Game
    save(game: Game) → Game
    list() → Game[]
  effects: [echo:write, echo:read]
```

## Operations

Pure operations (no effects, no service dependencies) — safe to call anywhere.

```op getLegalMoves
  desc: Returns legal target squares for the piece on the given square.
  input:
    board: Board
    square: Square
  output: Square[]
  errors:
    EmptySquare: no piece on square
    WrongSide: piece does not belong to the active side
  requires: [ChessEngine]
```

```op validateMove
  desc: Checks a move against chess rules without mutating state.
  input:
    board: Board
    move: Move
  output: Move
  errors:
    IllegalMove: move violates chess rules
    WrongTurn: piece does not belong to the active side
    GameOver: game has already ended
  requires: [ChessEngine]
```

```op applyMove
  desc: Applies a validated move and returns the next board state.
  input:
    board: Board
    move: Move                  # must be pre-validated
  output: Board
  requires: [ChessEngine]
  note: does not persist; use submitMove for the full transactional flow
```

Effectful operations — mutate persistent state.

```op startGame
  desc: Creates a new Game with two players and an initial Board.
  input:
    white: Player
    black: Player
  output: Game
  effects: [echo:write]
  requires: [GameStore]
```

```op submitMove
  desc: Validates and applies a move, then persists the updated Game.
  input:
    game: Game
    player: Player
    move: Move
  output: Game
  errors:
    WrongTurn: player is not the active side
    IllegalMove: move violates chess rules
    GameOver: game has already ended
  effects: [echo:write]
  requires: [ChessEngine, GameStore]
  note: |
    Composes validateMove → applyMove → GameStore.save.
    Atomic: Game is not persisted if validation fails.
```

```op resignGame
  desc: Player forfeits; opponent wins.
  input:
    game: Game
    player: Player
  output: Game                  # Game.status === finished, Game.winner set
  errors:
    GameOver: game has already ended
  effects: [echo:write]
  requires: [GameStore]
```

## Features

```feat F-5: Move Validation

  req F-5.1:
    when: Gameboard calls submitMove
    then: op:validateMove runs before any state change

  req F-5.2:
    when: validation fails
    then: error returned to caller; Game state unchanged

  req F-5.3:
    when: square is selected on Gameboard
    then: op:getLegalMoves called; results drive component:Gameboard.highlights
```

```feat F-6: Game Persistence

  req F-6.1:
    when: op:startGame completes
    then: Game written to ECHO and visible in component:Lobby game list

  req F-6.2:
    when: op:submitMove completes
    then: updated Game replicated to all peers via ECHO

  req F-6.3:
    when: peer receives a Game update
    then: component:Gameboard re-renders with new Board state
    tags: [collaborative]
```

## Acceptance

```test T-6: Submit valid move
  given: active game, white's turn, white player logged in
  when: white submits pawn e2→e4
  then:
    - op:validateMove returns move without error
    - Board updated: e4 occupied by white pawn, e2 empty
    - Game.board.turn === black
    - Game persisted to ECHO
```

```test T-7: Submit invalid move rejected atomically
  given: active game, white's turn
  when: white submits an illegal move (e2→e5)
  then:
    - IllegalMove error returned
    - Game.board unchanged
    - no ECHO write occurs
```

```test T-8: Legal moves highlighted
  given: new game, white's turn, Gameboard shown
  when: player selects e2
  then:
    - op:getLegalMoves returns [e3, e4]
    - Gameboard.highlights === [e3, e4]
```

